Railway one-time seed command:

Your start script already runs prisma db push on every deploy. To seed once and not repeat it, use the Railway CLI to run it as a one-off command — it won't touch your start command:


# Install Railway CLI if you haven't
npm i -g @railway/cli

# Login
railway login

# Link to your project (run from repo root)
railway link

# Run the seed once in the Railway environment
railway run npm run db:seed
This runs node dist/prisma/seed.js directly in Railway's environment (with your DB env vars) without changing the service's start command. No cleanup needed — it's a one-shot command, not a persistent config change.

Note: npm run db:seed runs the compiled dist/prisma/seed.js, so make sure you've pushed a build that includes the compiled seed file, or run railway run npm run build && npm run db:seed if the dist isn't up to date.

